{
  "stem": "24885.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came in, maybe 10 or 20, emptied out-- my father had a complete set of [NON-ENGLISH], of Talmud books, and they thought they were in the rabbi's house when they saw all the Bibles.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A great big section with all the books.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Threw it all out the window, built a fire downstairs, and burned all the stuff.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they threw out all the food we used to hide.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't have refrigeration then, but it was in the winter time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "April was still cold for I know the guards were still frozen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was snow outside.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They threw out all the food through the window and burned everything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On top of it, I was beaten up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I saw a picture of myself trying to escape up to another floor, but I never could find it anymore, which some of the Germans took.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Next morning, the people outside didn't know what to do, so they called-- they went to the Jewish commander, to the Jewish office-- which they had established-- to come.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And finally they left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The next morning my mother was called to the courthouse, which was a German judge, and the head of the-- president of Jewish office.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And my mother happened to recognize, because she wasn't home, she came in later, that she recognized some of the pilots, pointed them out.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They denied it, and for this the town was assessed another-- I don't remember the amount, 30,000 of 50,000 Polish zlotys, or 100,000, that we had to pay, because we accuse Germans of doing stuff like this.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean literally, they took the dignity and everything away from you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they were not SS.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were strictly from the flyers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Air force.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a Sunday afternoon something to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Beat up on the Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
